  "description": {
    "en": {
      "provenance": "imported",
      "value": "i) Rehabilitate/constructe Launching aprons and spurs of the 18 Kms long dykes at appropriate locations ; ii) Increase Height of the dyke at appropriate places ; iii) Debris collected below the Lothar bridge is removed and is used for increasing the height of the dyke; iv) Appropriate protection works on some inner streams are carried out.v) Intake of the irrigation canal is adjusted to the new river levels; vi) a study for a long term and sustainable solution with recommendation is available; ii) DDC representatives and the main political parties lobby for budget for the implementation of the recommendation of the study."
    },
